# Conventional Commits

When creating git commits in this repo, follow Conventional Commits. Husky runs commitlint on `commit-msg` and rejects non-compliant messages.

## Format

```
type(scope): short imperative summary

Optional body wrapped at 100 chars per line.
```

- Subject (header) max **100** characters (prefer ~72).
- Body lines max **100** characters each.
- Imperative mood: `add`, `fix`, `improve` — not `added` / `adds`.
- Scope optional: `reader`, `tts`, `ci`, etc.

## Types and releases

| Type | Bump on `main` |
| --- | --- |
| `feat` | minor |
| `fix` | patch |
| `feat!` / `BREAKING CHANGE:` | major |
| `perf` | patch |
| `docs`, `chore`, `refactor`, `style`, `test`, `ci` | none |

## Examples

```
feat(reader): add playback bookmarks

Implement bookmarking in the Reader so users can set, jump to, and
manage bookmarks during playback.
```

```
fix(tts): recover from cancelled chunk generation
```

## Avoid

```
# ❌ header too long / essay in subject
feat: implement bookmarking functionality in Reader component, allowing users to set, jump to, and manage bookmarks during playback, enhancing navigation and user experience

# ❌ body line over 100 chars
feat: add playback bookmarks

implement bookmarking functionality in Reader component, allowing users to set, jump to, and manage bookmarks during playback
```

Do not bump `package.json` version in local commits — semantic-release does that on `main`.
